                <div class="back-next-inpage-navigation-left-text" onclick="sectionSwapAdv('standard',true);">Standard Configuration Pricing</div>                <div class="back-next-inpage-navigation-right-arrow" onclick="sectionSwapAdv('storage',true);"></div>
                <div class="back-next-inpage-navigation-right-text" onclick="sectionSwapAdv('storage',true);">Additional Storage Pricing</div></div></div>

<div class="swapable-text" id="storage-text">


<h2>Additional Storage Pricing</h2>
    <p>Need more storage for your cloud server? Add SAN or Local Disk secondary storage to any CloudLayer Computing Instance.</p>

    <p>As Portable Storage Volumes, your secondary storage persists separately from the life of your cloud server, so you have the flexibility to easily move the volume from one cloud server to another—even between SoftLayer data centers. They’re useful for database applications that require access to raw, unformatted block-level storage and for moving large data sets between cloud servers.</p>

    <p><em>Note: SAN storage can accommodate up to four Portable Storage Volumes. Local Disk storage can accommodate one Portable Storage Volume.</em></p>

    <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" summary="Additional Storage Options" class="price2">
